A RESOLUTION
1 Commending the National Coalition of 100 Black Women Inc. and the 100 Black Men of
2 America Inc. and recognizing March 25, 2025, as their Joint Day at the Georgia State
3 Capitol; and for other purposes.
4 WHEREAS, the National Coalition of 100 Black Women Inc. (NCBW100) and the 100
5 Black Men of America Inc. are two of the nation's most esteemed advocacy and mentorship
6 organizations, committed to advancing equity, education, and economic empowerment for
7 African Americans; and
8 WHEREAS, the National Coalition of 100 Black Women Inc., under the esteemed leadership
9 of National President Virginia Harris, has dedicated itself to empowering Black women and
10 girls through education, health, economic development, and civic engagement through its
11 Georgia-based chapters, including the Decatur DeKalb Chapter, MECCA Chapter,
12 Metropolitan Atlanta Chapter, Northwest Georgia Chapter, Savannah Chapter, and Stone
13 Mountain Lithonia Chapter; and
14 WHEREAS, the Stone Mountain Lithonia Chapter of NCBW100 is serving as the host
15 chapter for this occasion with Cecilia Anderson as its president and under the leadership of
