16 Dr. Dee Dawkins-Haigler as the chair of the event, with Teresa Hardy and Frieda Aiden
17 serving as co-chairs; and
18 WHEREAS, the 100 Black Men of America Inc., led by Chairman of the Board Milton H.
19 Jones Jr., has made an immeasurable impact in mentoring and uplifting young African
20 American men through its Georgia-based chapters, including the 100 Black Men of Albany
21 Southwest Georgia Inc.; 100 Black Men of Atlanta Inc.; 100 Black Men of Augusta Inc.; 100
22 Black Men of Columbus, GA, Inc.; 100 Black Men of DeKalb Inc.; 100 Black Men of
23 Douglasville Inc.; 100 Black Men of Macon-Middle Inc.; 100 Black Men of
24 Milledgeville-Oconee Inc.; 100 Black Men of New Rock Georgia Inc.; 100 Black Men of
25 North Metro Inc.; 100 Black Men of Rome-NW GA Inc.; 100 Black Men of Savannah Inc.;
26 100 Black Men of South Metro Inc.; 100 Black Men of Southeast GA Inc.; 100 Black Men
27 of Valdosta Inc.; 100 Black Men of Warner Robins Inc.; and 100 Black Men of West
28 Georgia Inc.
29 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
30 the members of this body commend the National Coalition of 100 Black Women Inc. and the
31 100 Black Men of America Inc. for their continued dedication and invaluable contributions
32 and recognize March 25, 2025, as their Joint Day at the Georgia State Capitol.
33 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
34 and directed to make appropriate copies of this resolution available for distribution to
35 Virginia Harris, National President of NCBW100; Milton H. Jones Jr., Chairman of the
36 Board of 100 Black Men of America Inc.; and the Stone Mountain Lithonia Chapter of
37 NCBW100.
